President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Maine due to severe storm and flooding that occurred from December 23 to December 24, 2022. This declaration allows federal assistance to be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Mr. William F. Roy of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) will coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.